Under this Directive, prohibited AI uses include:

a. Relying on AI outputs as the sole basis for law enforcement actions, civil enforcement actions, or denial of government benefits;  
b. Using AI data or deploying AI to make decisions based on unlawful or improper consideration of protected characteristics;  
c. Improperly profiling, targeting, or discriminating based on individual characteristics or in retaliation for exercising Constitutional rights;  
d. Using AI for unlawful or improper monitoring, surveillance, or tracking of individuals;  
e. Providing DHS data or AI outputs to third parties for prohibited AI uses; and  
f. Other uses prohibited by applicable laws and policies.
